      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ADMITTED (4) was too slick last start, using his early speed to take control and kick strongly late to score by nearly 2 lengths over 1000m here 4 weeks ago. He maps to push forward again, and he is poised to repeat the dose. HEART AND SPIRIT (9) raced close to the pace last start before fading late to finish near the rear of a small field, but she has a top senior hoop replacing an apprentice this time, and she can bounce straight back into the money. TROIKA (1) was not far away when resuming at Ipswich over 1100m a month ago, and he generally improves with a run under his belt. He drops in class, and with a 2kg claim to help offset his weight rise, he can figure in the top 3 this time. LOST HIS BEANS (2) has not won for a while but loves this track, winning all of his 5 starts here. Dropping back to 1000m is the key, and in this easier company, a form reversal is on the cards.",
